OL,4,Coverspend, O'Dowd tells MLAs
OL,6,F"Given that any overspend this year
OL,7,Fwill be deducted from the Executive's
OL,8,Ffunding in 2026-27, every minister
OL,9,Fmust redouble efforts to identify
OL,10,Fefficiencies to help manage the
OL,11,Foverall financial position."
OL,13,FCommittee chairman Matthew O'Toole
OL,14,Fasked what the current level of the
OL,15,Fprojected overspend was.
OL,17,FMr O'Dowd said: "We are currently at a
OL,18,Ffigure of #387 million.
