OL,4,Coverspend, O'Dowd tells MLAs
OL,6,F"That is a pressure at this moment of
OL,7,Ftime and we wait on the provisional
OL,8,Fout-turns from our departments, and
OL,9,Fthey will change, hopefully for the
OL,10,Fbetter, over the next coming months.
OL,12,F"I have engagement around the
OL,13,FExecutive table with my Executive
OL,14,Fcolleagues and elsewhere.
OL,16,F"My constant message to them is we
OL,17,Fneed to drive down that overspend as
OL,18,Fit will result, due to Treasury rules,
OL,19,Fto us losing any overspends from next
OL,20,Fyear's budget, and next year's budget
OL,21,Fis particularly tight.
