OL,4,Coverspend, O'Dowd tells MLAs
OL,6,FMr O'Toole asked how realistic it was
OL,7,Fthat those overspends could be managed
OL,8,Fdown.
OL,10,FThe minister said: "I can't
OL,11,Fmicromanage each of the departments,
OL,12,Fnor is that my role.
OL,14,F"Ministers and their accounting
OL,15,Fofficers will know better than me the
OL,16,Fareas in which they can bear down on
OL,17,Fin terms of seeking efficiencies.
OL,19,F"It is up to those individual
OL,20,Fministers to continue to engage
OL,21,Fdirectly with their spending areas."
